      "message": "Storing password in plain text in a config repository readable by hundreds/thousands of people is not great.\n\nCrimson solved this by moving db config into /admin/settings, which is accessible only by GAE level admins. It also simplified running the code locally. https://screenshot.googleplex.com/DKztCtFOUqn.png\n\nPlease reuse this code... https://chrome-internal.googlesource.com/infra/infra_internal/+/master/go/src/infra_internal/crimson/server/crimsondb/crimsondb.go#737\n\nIf you choose not not reuse it, make sure machine-db still can run locally on devserver. It is much easier to modify stuff if it can be done locally.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 16,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 16,
