      "writtenOn": "2017-11-01T00:19:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I see, I thought that reviewed and versioned config would be better than configuring it via web UI but I wasn\u0027t sure the best way to store this password in a way that the app would be able to see it but the password was still sufficiently \"secret\". I will change it to be configured via /admin/settings.\n\nWhy do we need to stand up local instances of the app which interact with user-specific dev databases? I was hoping that rather than local instances for each person we\u0027d just use the -dev AppEngine instance (machine-db-dev). For comparison, I have never once started Machine Provider locally (besides unit tests).",
      "parentUuid": "bb95ae93_c81fa8d9",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 16,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 16,
        "endChar": 21
      },
      "revId": "a4032132b9506e5437aefac4d9a8fd62f87975b7",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
